This file is intended to guide a new user to this project through producing interacting with the project.

This project intends to use persistent homology, and topological data analysis to detect patterns between
macroeconomic variables. These patterns will then be employed to predict recessions.

Topological data analysis relies on topological strucutres between observations in n-space. In English,
this means that rather than looking at joint covariation (correlation), we'll be looking at the "shapes"
that the data makes, and compare those shapes across time periods in our dataset. For example, we may be
interested in how a point cloud suddenly no longer exists the months before a recession.

In terms of replicability, due to the nature of the visualizations that our project employs (most are in 3d or have interactive elements),
it is difficult to create a standard "output" and "temp folder" that works well for the reproducability exercise
for ECNS 560/460. The only replicatable visual is a data coverage map showing the coverage of the data that we have over time.
The code to produce this visual is located in the "missing values" section of the 
"clean_data.R" script.

With that said, the scripts to run in order to replicate our data are as follows:

1) raw_data_procurement.R
2) merge_data.R
3) clean_data.R
4) alter_data.R

***** It is worth noting that a key is required to run the raw_data_procurement.R
script. The script has brief instructions on top regardless.

The scripts "EDA.R" and "clean_data.R" are the workhorses of the exploratory analysis
for this project, and should be observed in conjunction with the draft document located
in the "output" folder.

